HOUSE BILL 1524
By Stevens
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 49,
Chapter 6, relative to searches on school property.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-6-4204(a), is amended by
deleting "subsection (a)" in subdivision (a)(2) and substituting "subdivision (a)(1)", designating
the subsection as subdivision (a)(1), and adding the following as a new subdivision:
(2) If a school conducts a security screening through a weapons detection
system and the weapons detection system triggers an alert on a container, package, or
other enclosure in the possession of a student or visitor, then a school employee who
has completed the training described in § 49-6-4212 and who is designated by the
principal to conduct a search for purposes of this subdivision (a)(2) may search the
container, package, or other enclosure that triggered the weapons detection system
alert. This subdivision (a)(2) does not authorize a search of an enclosure that is part of a
student's or visitor's clothing for which the student or visitor is wearing.
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-6-4212(a)(3), is amended by
deleting the subdivision and substituting:
(3) A school administrator or school employee designated by a school principal
for purposes of § 49-6-4204(a)(2) must complete the orientation and training developed
by the department pursuant to subdivision (a)(1) prior to conducting a search pursuant to
§ 49-6-4204(a)(1)(B)(iii), § 49-6-4204(a)(2), or § 49-6-4205(a)(2)(C).
SECTION 3. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
